# Rust Backend

## Modules

- `lib.rs` — system telemetry (sysinfo, DXGI, WMI), background threads, `emit("telemetry-update")`, `emit("gaming-latency-update")`, Tauri commands
- `gaming_latency.rs` — ICMP ping gateway + `1.1.1.1`, TCP `:443` fallback, jitter (15 samples), verdicts; thread every **2 s**
- `dns.rs` — TCP ping port 53, IP whitelist, `tokio::sync::Mutex` single-flight (queue, don't reject)
- `drivers.rs` — WMI scan (PowerShell), blacklist VM/VPN/périphériques, `collapse_simplified_primary()` (3 max), `is_relevant_for_full_mode`
- `driver_updates.rs` — Windows Update COM enrichment + `DetectNow` ; `resolve_update_candidate()` (WU-first si versions égales) ; `open_windows_update_settings()` → `ms-settings:windowsupdate`
- `driver_store.rs` — `pnputil /enum-drivers` fallback for store versions
- `driver_version.rs` — multi-format version comparison
- `security.rs` — antivirus detection via WMI `ROOT\SecurityCenter2` / `AntiVirusProduct`; fallback registry Defender

## Telemetry thread

- Runs in `setup()` → `std::thread::spawn`, 1 s tick
- Updates `Arc<Mutex<SharedMonitorState>>` then `app_handle.emit(TELEMETRY_EVENT, &SystemInfo)`
- GPU WMI metrics every 2 s; network list refresh every 30 ticks
- `get_system_info` clones state under brief lock — IPC fallback for frontend

## Gaming latency thread

- Separate `std::thread::spawn` in `setup()`, **2 s** tick
- `GamingLatencyTracker::sample()` — gateway via PowerShell `Get-NetRoute` / `route print` fallback
- Internet: ICMP `ping -n 1 -w 800 1.1.1.1`, fallback TCP connect `:443`
- Jitter: std dev over rolling 15 internet samples; verdict in French labels
- State in `GamingLatencyState` (`Arc<Mutex<GamingLatencySnapshot>>`); command `get_gaming_latency`
- Subprocess flags: `CREATE_NO_WINDOW` (`0x08000000`) on Windows

## Security Detection

- Refresh every **60 s** in background thread (not every 1 s telemetry tick)
- `product_state & 0x1000` → enabled; prefer third-party AV over Defender when both listed
- Normalize display names (strip WMI GUID prefix, `Microsoft Defender` for Windows Defender)
- Exposed as `SystemInfo.security: { is_protected, product_name }`

## DNS

- `ALLOWED_DNS_IPS` — reject IPC requests to arbitrary hosts (anti port-scan)
- Concurrent pings serialized via async mutex (second call waits)

## Driver Scan Rules

- Safe UX labels only: `"Installed"`, `"Verify Online"`, `"Update Available"` (when newer version detected)
- Exclude virtual/VM/VPN devices and interface peripherals (mice, keyboards, headsets)
- **Simplified (`simplified=true`):** categories Graphics/Network/Bluetooth only → **1 primary per category** (discrete GPU, Ethernet before Wi‑Fi)
- **Full (`simplified=false`):** + Audio, Storage, Firmware; physical PCI/USB/ACPI/SCSI/HDAUDIO only
- Cache in `DriverCacheState` with **5 min TTL**; `force=true` bypasses cache (required on mode toggle)
- `spawn_blocking` for PowerShell — never block async runtime; driver scan can take **60–90 s** (WU)
- **`DriverInfo.update_source`:** `"windows_update"` | `"driver_store"` | `""` — set by `enrich_drivers_with_updates()`
- **`resolve_update_candidate()`:** prefer WU when both sources have same/newer version; store-only when WU has no match or store is strictly newer
- Tauri command `open_windows_update` — triggers `DetectNow` then opens Windows Update settings

## GPU Metrics

Native Windows: DirectX DXGI (static VRAM/name) + WMI (`Win32_PerfFormattedData_GPUPerformanceCounters_*`) every 2 s.

## Serialization

Rust structs in `lib.rs` mirror TypeScript types in `src/types/index.ts`. Keep field names in sync (snake_case in Rust, same in JSON).

## Network Interfaces

- Exclude virtual adapters in `lib.rs` (`is_virtual_interface`: Hyper-V, Docker, VPN, loopback, etc.)
- Each `NetworkInterface` includes `kind`: `"wifi"` | `"ethernet"` | `"other"` via `classify_interface(name)`
- Speed totals aggregate physical interfaces only
- Frontend picks primary interface by highest `received + transmitted` traffic

## Tauri security

- CSP set in `tauri.conf.json` (not `null`)
- Capabilities: `src-tauri/capabilities/default.json` — window + opener permissions only
